given only in relative units and measurements were
made on sample with relatively big additions of W+Te
Tandem Van de Graaff accelerator of
the University and the Technical University of Munich.
An unpolarized deuteron beam.
The integration of the beam current in a
Faraday cup allowed the determination of absolute
cross sections.
The isotopically enriched target (99.8%) with a
thickness 120 mu-g/cm2 was prepared by vacuum
evaporation on a 4 mu-g/cm2 thick carbon backing.
Reaction products were momentum-separated
by the Q3D spectrograph within a solid angle
acceptance of up to 7 msr and detected in a 890 mm
long position sensitive cathode strip detector
